Task 1: Install Ansible on the Control Node
Objective: Install Ansible on the Linux machine.

Steps:

Open the terminal and run the following commands to install Ansible on your system:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible
Verify the installation:

ansible --version
Task 2: Set up a Basic Inventory
Objective: Create a basic inventory file to list managed hosts.

Steps:

Create an inventory file by running:

sudo nano /etc/ansible/hosts
Add a line for the managed host (localhost in this case):

[local]
localhost ansible_connection=local
Save the file and exit the editor.

Task 3: Run a Simple Ping Command
Objective: Test the Ansible setup by running a "ping" command on the managed host.

Steps:

Run the following Ansible ping command to check connectivity:

ansible local -m ping
If successful, Ansible will return a pong response.

